@page "/list"
<PageTitle>List - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="list">List (Ul / Li)</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Ul and Li components render semantic unordered list elements with
                design-system-aware styling.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Ul&gt;
    &lt;Li&gt;First item&lt;/Li&gt;
    &lt;Li&gt;Second item&lt;/Li&gt;
    &lt;Li&gt;Third item&lt;/Li&gt;
&lt;/Ul&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="programmatic-lists">Programmatic Lists</h2>

            <p>
                Use the Foreach or ListOf base components to render lists from data collections.
                See the <a href="render-foreach">Render &amp; Foreach</a> page.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="list-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 List</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 List</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the Ul component maps to a list-group container and each Li
                maps to a list-group-item. This produces Bootstrap's styled list with borders
                and appropriate padding. You can apply additional Bootstrap list-group modifiers
                such as list-group-item-action or list-group-item-primary through the
                Specialization parameter on individual Li components.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="list-daisyui">DaisyUI List</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI List</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the Ul component maps to a menu container and each Li maps to a
                menu item. DaisyUI's menu component supports vertical and horizontal layouts
                and is commonly used inside drawers and dropdowns. The menu class and
                its modifier variants such as menu-horizontal or menu-compact are available
                through the Specialization parameter.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="list-basecoat">Basecoat List</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat List</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the Ul and Li components are styled with Tailwind utility classes
                that produce a clean list layout. The default styling removes list-style markers
                and applies consistent vertical spacing between items. You can restore markers,
                adjust spacing, or add borders and backgrounds through the Class or Specialization
                parameters on either the Ul or individual Li components.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("list", "List (Ul / Li)"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("programmatic-lists", "Programmatic Lists", 2),
    new TocItem("list-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 List", 2),
    new TocItem("list-daisyui", "DaisyUI List", 2),
    new TocItem("list-basecoat", "Basecoat List", 2)
])" />

</div>
